    "step 3": {
        "implementation details": "III. Overview of Microarray Platform Used:\n\u2460 The microarray data was based on the GPL96 platform, specifically the Affymetrix Human Genome U133A Array (Affymetrix Inc., Santa Clara, CA, USA).\n\u2461 This platform allows for the simultaneous detection of thousands of genes and was utilized to analyze the gene expression profiles of the collected samples.\n\u2462 The use of this platform is critical for obtaining reliable and reproducible results in the context of the study's objectives.\n\u2463 Quality control measures, including RNA degradation and 3'/5' ratio testing, are standard practices that ensure the reliability of the data produced.",
        "original text": "The platform information on these microarray data is as follows: GPL96, Affymetrix Human Genome U133A Array (Affymetrix Inc., Santa Clara, CA, USA).",
